	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I haven't had time to work on this compo's cartridge release because of other obligations, such as something that will see limited release at an upcoming convention, as well as translated version of a previously released game. Heck, I didn't even judge this time.<br /><br />So anyway, up to 480 KiB of entries will fit on a 4 Mbit cartridge. But we appear to have more than that, and <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=189743#p189743" class="postlink">infiniteneslives explained</a> that with a 3 volt memory, we can go up to 32 Mbit.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


